<paragraph blockId="6.[167,780,1323,1997]" pageId="6" pageNumber="607">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1536,1560]" pageId="6" pageNumber="607">Identification.</emphasis>
A small species of dasyatid (maximal disc width less than 
<quantity box="[400,494,1570,1594]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="607" unit="mm" value="180.0">180 mm</quantity>
); snout elongate, forming a projecting tip; anterior disc margins slightly concave; eye small; large band of compact denticles running along centre of the disc to the tail sting; dorsal surface of the disc light grey-brown, paler on margins, ventral side of the disc white (
<bibRefCitation author="Carpenter KE &amp; Niem VH" box="[334,627,1738,1762]" pageId="6" pageNumber="607" pagination="1397 - 2068" refId="ref26752" refString="Carpenter KE, Niem VH (Eds.) (1999 a) FAO species identification guide for fishery purposes. The living marine resources of the Western Central Pacific. Volume 3. Batoid fishes, chimaeras and bony fishes part 1 (Elopidae to Linophrynidae). FAO, Rome, Italy, pp. 1397 - 2068." type="book chapter" year="1999">Carpenter and Niem 1999a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[167,780,1323,1997]" pageId="6" pageNumber="607">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[206,416,1771,1795]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="607" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walga">
<emphasis box="[206,416,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="607">Brevitrygon walga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other stingrays occurring in this region by its large band of compact denticles running along centre of disc. A common coastal species in Southeast Asia regularly occurring in brackish environments. Generic classifica- tion follows 
<bibRefCitation author="Last PR &amp; Naylor G &amp; Manjaji-Matsumoto BM" box="[300,479,1939,1963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="607" pagination="345 - 368" refId="ref27813" refString="Last PR, Naylor G, Manjaji-Matsumoto BM (2016) A revised classification of the family Dasyatidae (Chondrichthyes: Myliobati- formes) based on new morphological and molecular insights. Zootaxa 4139: 345 - 368. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4139.3.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Last et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
; this species was previously classified in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[409,527,1974,1997]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Himantura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="607" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[409,527,1974,1997]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="607">Himantura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Weigmann S" box="[591,768,1973,1997]" pageId="6" pageNumber="607" pagination="249 - 312" refId="ref28882" refString="Weigmann S (2011) Contribution to the taxonomy and distribution of eight ray species (Chondrichthyes, Batoidea) from coastal waters of Thailand. Verhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg 46: 249 - 312. https: // doi. org / 10.5402 / 2012 / 860768" type="journal article" year="2011">Weigmann 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
